review_blob: 33cl bottle at the LOT Business Lounge, Warsaw on 29-Apr-2016. Refreshing pale lager with grassy notes, lightly hopped and a slight sweet malt taste. Not bad for a lager,

50cl bottle (shared) at Cafe Foksal, Warsaw on 28-Apr-2016. Hazy pale colour with a medium sized white head. Grassy aroma which follows through on tasting. Light body and medium carbonation. Nothing to it really - quite disappointing.

50cl bottle at Cafe Foksal, Warsaw on 28-Apr-2016. Hazy dark amber colour with a medium sized off-white head. Aroma of pine, sweet malt and citrus fruits. Medium body and soft/medium carbonation.Sweetish taste of caramel, malt, tropical fruit and floral hops. Pretty good balance, but perhaps just a little too much caramel. Refreshing to have a nice local imperial IPA after drinking more average Polish beer on my trip.

50cl bottle at Signature, Warsaw on 28-Apr-2016. Pale golden yellow colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of yeast, grass and grain. Light body and carbonation.Sweet taste with a bittersweet finish. Lots of grassy notes. Not a favourite.

50cl bottle at Signature, Warsaw on 28-Apr-2016. Ruby brown colour with a medium sized tan coloured head. Aroma of sweet caramel malt, spices and hops. Medium to full body and soft carbonation. Slightly sweet - molasses, caramel, malt and hops. A little heavy.

33cl bottle, purchased at The Bierkoning, Amsterdam and consumed on 27-Apr-2016. Hazy golden colour with a medium sized off-white head. Floral aroma - citrus, pine and sweet fruit. Light body and medium carbonation. Flavour of tropical fruit, citrus, sweet malt and hops. A nice bittersweet mouthfeel with a lingering bitterness. A very good pale ale. So much flavour - surprised its only 4.6% ABV.  Pretty close to the gluten free version.

33cl at Delirium Cafe, Amsterdam on 27-Apr-2016. Label - 6% ABV. Slightly hazy pale blonde colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of floral hops, fruit and alcohol. Medium body and carbonation. Lots of citrus fruits, slightly sweet but a little hop bitterness. Pretty standard Belgian ale.

Draught at Delirium Cafe, Amsterdam on 27-Apr-2016. Hazy reddish brown colour with a tan coloured head. Aroma of pine, caramel malt and spices. Medium body and soft carbonation. Fruity with caramel, malt and rye. Light sweetness, with a bitter finish.  Nice hop balance, Very enjoyable.

Draught at Delirium Cafe, Amsterdam on 27-Apr-2016. Clear pale blonde colour with a thick white head. Aroma of flora, fruit and alcohol. Medium body and carbonation. Fruity flavour - slightly tart apple, and a bitter hoppy finish.

33cl bottle from De Bierkoning, Amsterdam on 26-Apr-2016. Hazy dark reddish amber colour with a large off-white head. Aroma of caramel malt and pine. Pretty lively carbonation and medium body. Lovely lacing. Taste of caramel, earl grey tea, malt and a nice bitter hop finish. Not a bad amber ale - although lacking depth.

Draught at Delirium Cafe on 25-Apr-2016. Clear golden amber colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of caramel, sweet fruit and pine. Medium body and carbonation. Sweetish taste of molasses, orange peel and lemon citrus. Slightly bitter alcoholic finish. Not a bad Belgian strong ale.

Draught at Delirium Cafe, Amsterdam on 25-Apr-2016. Cloudy pale amber colour with a small white head. Aroma of citrus, floral pine and wheat. Medium body and carbonation. Slightly bitter fruity flavour. Barley, malt, orange peel Light bitterness, but slightly oversweet. Nice hoppy fruity Wit, but best sipped..

33cl bottle brought at the brewery shop and poured into a snifter glass on 23-Apr-2016. A dark brown colour with a thick tan head which settles down. Aroma of sour fruit (cherry), coffee and hops. Medium sticky body and softly carbonated. Sweet cocoa flavour, with coffee, caramel and malt, tart fruit and a bittersweet sticky finish. Pretty damn good.

33cl bottle from the brewery store, consumed fresh on 22-Apr-2016. Hazy pale amber colour with a small white head. Aroma of citrus - lemon and oranges, banana and wheat. Light to medium body and carbonation. Light citrus taste with a nice bitterness. Orange peel, lemongrass and banana. Coriander and spices. Light sweetness. A nice fruity wheat ale.

33cl bottle from De Bierkoning, Amsterdam on 22-Apr-2016. Hazy orange colour with a medium sized off-white head. Aroma of bitter tangerine, yeast and spices. Medium body and carbonation. Creamy mouthfeel. Bitter tangy fruit flavour and medium caramel sweetness. A lovely well balanced beer.

33cl bottle on 16-Apr-2016, poured into a long stemmed tulip glass. Hazy light pale amber colour with a medium sized white head which dissipates quickly. Aroma of sweet malt and spices. Light body and medium carbonation. Upfront taste of pepper, lemon citrus and malt. Light, refreshing but not one I would buy regularly.

Draught pint at The Globe, Hong Kong on 21-Mar-2016. Hazy golden amber colour. Aroma of sweet malt and pine. Light body and carbonation. Flavour of sweet biscuit malt, hops and citrus. A floral hoppy IPA. Refreshing and sessionable; nice bitter finish.
beer_name: Hong Kong Beer Co. Lucky Monkey (Crooked Island Cask Series)

review_blob: 30cl draught (2016 seasonal) at the brewery taproom on 16-Apr-2016. Dark brown / black in colour with a medium sized tan coloured head. Aroma of malt, spices and pine. Medium body and carbonation. Caramel malt and hops up-front. Some chocolate, spices and smoke. Bittersweet finish.  A nice cascade black IPA.

30cl draught (2016 seasonal) at the brewery taproom on 16-Apr-2016. Deep red amber colour with a medium sized off-white head. Aroma of malt, hops and fruit. Medium body and carbonation. Caramel malt up-front and medium hopped. Light flavour of spices and rye. Slightly dry but refreshing.

33cl bottle picked up in Albert Heijn (Amsterdam), and poured into a long stemmed tulip glass on 15-Apr-2016. Clear brown colour with a small white head. Lovely lacing. Aroma of spices, sweet malt and yeast. Medium body and carbonation. Favour of hops, seer malt, caramel, and fruit. Bittersweet finish. Nice hoppy taste - big fan of this beer. A really good Belgian tribute to the West Coast (amber ale) style.

33cl bottle picked up at the brewery and poured into a snifter glass on 15-Apr-2016.  Dark brown, almost black in colour with a small tan coloured head. Aroma of sweet chocolate, spices and hops. Full body and soft carbonation. Flavour heavy in bitter dark chocolate, molasses, dark fruit, tobacco and vanilla. Creamy bittersweet mouthfeel. A really nice ale - similar in character to an imperial stout. Excellent.
beer_name: De Molen / Hair of the Dog Adam

review_blob: On draught (keg) at the Craft Beer Co., Clerkenwell on 14-Apr-2016. Hazy orange amber colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of peaches, passion fruit and pine. Medium body and carbonation. Sweet tropical fruit flavours and lots of floral hops. A pretty good and refreshing IPA.
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Simcoe Sticklebract

review_blob: On draught at the The Craft Beer Co. Clerkenwell on 14-Apr-2016. Clear dark golden amber colour with a small white head. Aroma of peaches, citrus and pine. Medium body and soft/medium carbonation. Flavours of peaches, tropical fruits, grapefruit, malt and hops. Slightly bitter, and good to sip. Complex - there is lot to this beer.

33cl bottle, poured into a matching long stemmed tulip glass. A Xmas gift from my eldest son. Dark reddish brown colour with a thick tan coloured head. Strong sweet smell of caramel, stewed dark fruits, sugar, and Belgian yeast. Full body and light carbonation. Sweet caramel and molasses on tasting, fruit and spices (which taste a little artificial). Sticky sweet and bitter finish.

33cl bottle, purchased at De Bierkoning, Amsterdam and poured on 12-Apr-2016. Very lively with lots of fizz. Hazy orange amber colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of sweet fruit, citrus and yeast. Medium body. Taste of caramel, biscuit, spices and hops. A sweetish beer in the style of a Belgian pale ale.

33cl bottle on 06-Apr-2016, picked up in Albert Heijn and poured into a stemmed tulip glass. Clear pale yellow colour with a thick white head. Aroma of pepper, spices, wheat and banana. Medium body and carbonation. Flavours of bananabread, yeast, malt and spices. Slightly sweet. Reminded me of La Chouffe. Pretty good.

33cl bottle on 05-Apr-2016, picked up in Berlin and poured into a long stemmed tulip glass. Hazy pale golden colour with a medium sized thick white head. Aroma of citrus, hops and sweet fruits. Medium body and carbonation. Juicy tropical taste and hoppy. Light bitterness.
UPDATED: APR 10, 2016

33cl bottle from De Bierkoening, Amsterdam. Served in a long stemmed tulip glass on 28-Mar-2016. Reddish amber colour with a medium sized white head which dussipates leaving nice lacing down the glass. Aroma of sweet fruit, berries and malt. Sweet malt, light honey sweetness, bitter grapefruit, tropical fruit flavours and floral hops, lasting tropical fruit and bitterness on the palate.
beer_name: Buxton / To l Collaboration Carnage (Samarbejds delggelse) 2014

review_blob: 33cl bottle from De Bierkoening, Amsterdam. Served in a long stemmed tulip glass on 28-Mar-2016. Reddish amber colour with a medium sized white head which dussipates leaving nice lacing down the glass. Aroma of sweet fruit, berries and malt. Sweet malt, light honey sweetness, bitter grapefruit, tropical fruit flavours and floral hops, lasting tropical fruit and bitterness on the palate.

Draught 2/3rd pint at the Beavertown tap room, Tottenham Hale on 02-Apr-2016. Clear pale colour with a small white head. Light to medium body and carbonation. Flavour of orange peel, grapefruit, passionfruit and mango. Good hop profile. Pretty refreshing.
beer_name: Beavertown Lupuloid IPA Series - Sgt. O Mors

review_blob: Draught pint at The Grove, Birmingham on 01-Apr-2016. Clear golden colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of sweet malt and fruit. Medium body and carbonation. Grajn, mslt and biscuit flavours. Sweet with light bitternes and hop profile.

12oz bottle brought back from San Francisco and consumed on 31-Mar-2016. Clear golden amber with a medium sized white head. Aroma heavy in citrus and pine. Medium body and carbonation. Flavour full of tropical notes and juicy hops. Passionfruit, gooseberry, mango and grapefruit. A,n excellent fruity imperial IPA.

33cl bottle at Cafe De Nord, Paris on 31-Mar-2016. Dark brown with a tan coloured head. Heavy sweetness in Aroma and flavour. Dark fruit, molasses, caramel. Heavy sweetness. Pretty commercial offering from Heineken France.
UPDATED: APR 15, 2016

Draught pint at Salt n Bone, Berlin on 25-Mar-2016. Hazy pale golden colour with a medium sized white head. Hoppy sweet Aroma. Medium body and carbonation. Caramel malt and grain. CItrus and hops lead. Tropical fruit sweetness and grapefruit bitterness. Refreshing.
33cl bottke at Taverna Appollon, Berlin on 25-Mar-2016. Yellow fizzy and bland with a medium sized white head. Lots of cereal, grass. Pretty boring.

12oz bottle at Arcona Living, Osnabruck, Germany on 24-Mar-2016. Dark, slmost black in colour with a medium sized tan coloured head. Sweet malt hoppy aroma. Full body and carbonation. Smoky, bitter and sweet. Nice dessert beer.

33cl bottle at Arcona Living, Osnabruck, Germany on 24-Mar-2016. Dark amber colour with a medium sized tan coloured head. Sweet malt hoppy aroma. Medium body and carbonation. Flavour of sweet bread malt, floral hops, grapefruit and tropical fruits. A pleasant surprise - pretty good.
UPDATED: APR 10, 2016

Draught pint at London City Airport on 23-Mar-2016. Reddish amber colour with a thin tan coloured head. Aroma of caramel, malt and pine. Medium body and carbonation. Light hop profile. Bread with heavy caramel malt sweetness. Pretty run of the mill bock.

33cl bottle at Instock restaurant, Amsterdam on 20-Mar-2016. Clear brown beer with a medium sized tan coloured head. Aroma of bread, sweet malt and pine. Sweet Belgian style IPA, heavy in nakt, caramel and floral hops. As it warms it leads to an amber ale profile. Backbone of brown bread with upfront bitterness and hops. Lovely.

30cl draught at the brewpub on 20-Mar-2016. Clear dark brown colour with a medium to thin tan coloured head. Aroma of chocolate and roasted coffee. Full body and soft carbonation. Spicy. Light sweetness. Fruity followed by a chocolate coffee taste which takes it home.

30cl draught at the brewpub on 20-Mar-2016. Hazy pale golden colour with a medium sized white head. Aroma of citrus pine and fruit. Light body and medium carbonation. Light fruity bitterness. Banana leading but hops overwhelming. Closer to a pale ale than a wit bier but lovely and refreshing.

30cl draught at the brewpub on 20-Mar-2016. Hazy orange amber colour with a medium sized tan coloured head. Aroma of sweet malt, dark fruits, warm spices and yeast which follow through on tasting. Light floral hops and full flavoured. Medium body and carbonation. Nice seasonal.

33cl bottle on 19-Mar-2016, poured into a long stemmed tulip glass. Hazy dark amber coloured beer with a medium sized white head. Aroma of caramel, pine and sweet malt. Medium body and carbonation. Caramel, malt and hops - pretty run of the mill American - style amber. Light and refreshing.
beer_name: Amsterdam Brewboys Hop Riot Amber Ale

review_blob: Draught point at Teds Montana Grill in NYC. Clear golden amber colour with a small white head. Aroma of citrus, hops and sweet malt. Light to medium body with good carbonation. Lovely fruity taste with a bitter finish. Heavily hopped, lots of tropical fruits - pineapple, passionfruit, with citrus (grapefruit). I love the grapefruit zest - really refreshing. Great with meat.

Draught (taster) at Bar Americain in NYC on 17-Mar-2016. Clear dark amber colour with a thin tan coloured head. Aroma of malt, caramel and I do get some (faint) bourbon and spices. Full body and soft/medium carbonation. Sweet flavour of malt, butterscotch and caramel. Some wood and vanilla. Not bad but tough to drink quickly.

Draught pint at Stephanies, Logan Airport, Boston on 16-Mar-2016. Dark ruby red colour with a thick tan coloured head. Aroma of sweet malt, pine and caramel. Medium to full body and soft carbonation. Bitter with sweet caramel malt and biscuit. Nice balance.

Draught pint at House of Shields, San Francisco on 15-Mar-2016. Clear amber colour with a thin white head. Medium body with light carbonation. Light hop bitterness. Lots if fruit with light hop bitterness. The heavy sweetness of the tropical fruit overwhelms this beer.
